<subSubSection id="C3606530B31A8A0EFCDAF819FD2CFE0E" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="9" pageNumber="74" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC536BBB31A8A0EFCDAF819FD2CFE0E" blockId="9.[835,1436,1789,1981]" lastBlockId="11.[181,783,207,398]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="9" pageNumber="74">
It is clear from the protologue that Urban did not have at his disposal a specimen with a flower (“flores non vidi”, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEB4B4AB3188A0EFE8BFF54FE5DFF69" author="Urban, I." box="[305,452,207,233]" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis" pageId="11" pageNumber="76" pagination="213 - 230" part="21" refId="ref14499" refString="Urban, I. 1925. Sertum antillanum XXIII. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 21: 213 - 230." title="Sertum antillanum XXIII" type="journal article" year="1925">Urban, 1925</bibRefCitation>
), and that he was describing this species from material in B that is no longer extant. The two rather scrappy sheets at S are both annotated “type”, but only one (S04-2941) has reproductive parts (one flower and two fruits in the packet). This sheet (
<figureCitation id="13412A3EB3188A0EFF44FEEFFED2FE0E" box="[254,331,372,398]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[151,185,1854,1875]" captionTargetBox="[204,1353,205,1826]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 3. a, lectotype of Solanum drymophilum O.E Schulz,Sintenis 2374 (BM000886627) (= S.ensifolium Dunal).Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum, London; b, lectoytpe of S. gundlachii O.E. Schulz, Wright 3030 (GH00077553). Reproduced with permission of Harvard University,Cambridge,Massachusetts, USA;c, lectotype of S. maestrense Urb.,Ekman 14456 (S04-2941). Reproduced with permission of the Swedish Museum of Natural History; d, lectotype of S. squarrosum O.E. Schulz, Schomburgk 51 (L0403808). Reproduced with permission of the Natural History Museum of the Netherlands." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6326314" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6326314/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="76">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
) is chosen here as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
